<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div class="portlet">
    <div class="portletBody portletContent">
      
      <img src="/++resource++info_icon.gif" />
      The build log is produced when we try to compile the source package
      into binary packages which can be installed on your distribution.
      There may not be a build log if this is a read-only distribution (one
      we just monitor but don't actually produce in the Launchpad, like
      Ubuntu and its derivatives).

    </div>
  </div>
</metal:leftportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1><span tal:replace="context/title"/> Build Log</h1>

  <p class="documentDescription">This page shows the build logs list for 
  all source package release uploaded in 
  <span tal:replace="context/distrorelease/title"/>.</p>

  <ul tal:repeat="release context/releases">
  <li tal:condition="release/builds">
  <p tal:content="release/title">TITLE</p>
    <ul>
      <li tal:repeat="build release/builds">
        <tal:block condition="build/buildlog"> 
        <a tal:attributes="href build/buildlog/url"
           tal:content="build/buildlog/filename">BUILDLOG</a>
        </tal:block>
        <tal:block condition="not: build/buildlog">
        <p> No buildlog for <span tal:replace="build/title">BUILD</span></p>
        </tal:block>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  </ul>

</div>
</body>
</html>
 
